<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="NVIDIA">
  <data key="d0">NVIDIA</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A company that pioneered accelerated computing and has expanded into various computationally intensive fields, including scientific computing, AI, data science, autonomous vehicles, robotics, and digital twin applications. It is a data center scale AI infrastructure company reshaping industries.&lt;SEP&gt;A company with products and services that function on a standalone basis and are involved in contracts with multiple performance obligations.&lt;SEP&gt;NVIDIA is a company that reports its financial data, including revenue and expenses, and has a focus on Compute &amp; Networking and Graphics segments.&lt;SEP&gt;NVIDIA is a company that has partnered with Arm for nearly two decades, as mentioned by Jensen Huang.&lt;SEP&gt;NVIDIA is a technology company utilizing Intel Xeon 6 processors in its DGX Rubin NVL8 systems for AI infrastructure.&lt;SEP&gt;NVIDIA is a competitor known for its GPUs, which play a significant role in the competitive landscape relevant to AI workloads.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0b30e55c2d2c942c8ef27807467b3d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f2ce3a4f3492cdc62d91339c8332500&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0fc487cdc1541b708566fbf837bf0441&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92916718cb73d1b7ba5306ed1ae35864&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8d9c25644243f4d529d06cf43465d4b4</data>
