<node id="Consolidated Financial Statements">
  <data key="d0">Consolidated Financial Statements</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Consolidated Financial Statements are comprehensive financial reports that provide a detailed view of a company's financial position, including assets, liabilities, equity, income, and expenses. They are part of the Annual Report on Form 10-K and include NVIDIA's financial data. These statements are based on historical and anticipated results, trends, and various assumptions deemed reasonable. The reports also encompass the financial data of a parent company and its subsidiaries, offering a holistic view of the entire organization's financial health.

In addition to the main financial figures, the Consolidated Financial Statements include various notes that provide detailed information on different aspects of the company's financial health. These notes discuss the company's credit facilities, debt, commitments, and other financial information. They also cover discussions on tax examinations, assessments, and related proceedings, offering a thorough understanding of the company's financial obligations and potential liabilities.

Overall, the Consolidated Financial Statements serve as a crucial tool for stakeholders to assess a company's financial performance and stability. By providing a comprehensive compilation of financial data and detailed notes, these statements enable investors, regulators, and other interested parties to make informed decisions based on a complete understanding of the company's financial position.&lt;SEP&gt;The Consolidated Financial Statements contain details on the company's financial covenants and debt obligations.&lt;SEP&gt;Consolidated Financial Statements are financial reports that include all subsidiaries' financial data and have not made significant accruals for customer audit or inspection contingencies.&lt;SEP&gt;The Consolidated Financial Statements are comprehensive financial reports that include details on goodwill and purchased intangible assets, and are part of the company's Annual Report on Form 10-K.&lt;SEP&gt;The consolidated financial statements are comprehensive financial reports that include the company's financial performance, including details on purchase commitments and contingencies.&lt;SEP&gt;Consolidated financial statements provide a comprehensive view of the financial position of a company and its subsidiaries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0b30e55c2d2c942c8ef27807467b3d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91ba0c40d4695fe5428e9f1aaee99693&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-217dcca296bd42c2a1d26c339d20ff32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26fa1d1070f941c3c83605779a2af8f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05ef57917f6bff8e91ef6130ec6229c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb113ac9e0cc9e74e5cc817ec0cd9a79&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d34b219513d1d4953f831b7693287834&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-706c3addabed1cbc496a03d35fbb0b1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1329332311e82d0b2cc6f7232bfaa092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c9d9262cc591e5a663ff1343e1ab5b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6646d6be107845318b9e01fd74b6a79&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0644a249b2d47b7e49a78f4bf359cb71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a5582252ed15279da3f293d02cea1b9</data>
