<node id="Research and Development">
  <data key="d0">Research and Development</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Research and Development (R&amp;D) is a crucial category for the company, representing both substantial financial investment and a core function necessary for future success. In the fiscal year 2025, R&amp;D expenses were recorded at $10,977 million, which increased dramatically to $18,497 million in fiscal year 2026, marking a 43% increase from the previous year. This financial trend highlights the company's growing commitment to innovation, product development, and technology advancement. 

The activities encompassed within R&amp;D are pivotal to the company’s objective of innovating and enhancing its product offerings. These activities not only include the creation of new products but also focus on securing design wins and maintaining market share in the face of competitive pressures. The significant resources allocated to R&amp;D reveal its integral role in the company’s overall strategy for growth and sustainability, impacting overall business performance. 

Additionally, R&amp;D is characterized by policies and organizational efforts directed toward innovative solutions. This category is directly connected to the expenses outlined in financial reports, ensuring transparency regarding the allocation of funds across different fiscal years. The increase in R&amp;D spending reflects a steadfast commitment to fostering innovation, which is essential for the company's long-term viability and success. Overall, R&amp;D involves investments and efforts to innovate and improve products and technologies, emphasizing its importance in the broader business context.&lt;SEP&gt;Research and development expenses increased by $141.8 million, primarily due to increased personnel costs and new product introduction costs.&lt;SEP&gt;Research and development encompass activities related to innovation and improvement of products, which are crucial for maintaining competitive advantage.</data>
