  <data key="d2">Interest income for fiscal year 2026 was $2,300 million, showing an increase from the previous year.&lt;SEP&gt;Interest Income is a category of income that increased by 5% for the company in the fiscal year ended March 31, 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Interest Income is a component of Other Expense (Income), Net, which increased by $17.1 million due to higher interest earning balances.&lt;SEP&gt;Interest income is an additional source of cash flow, influenced by higher cash balances and higher interest rates.&lt;SEP&gt;Interest income for the year ended December 31, 2025, was $383.4 million, a 23.3% increase from the previous year, due to higher cash and marketable securities balances.&lt;SEP&gt;Interest income increased by $158.6 million, due to higher cash and marketable securities balances and investment yields.</data>
