<node id="Interest Expense">
  <data key="d0">Interest Expense</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Interest Expense represents the cost incurred by an entity when borrowing money, specifically highlighting the associated costs with various debt instruments held. For the fiscal year 2026, Interest Expense was recorded at $(259) million, which reflects a slight increase from the previous year’s amount. In fiscal year 2025, the total Interest Expense was $302,166 thousand, which marked a decrease of $(9,087) thousand compared to the previous fiscal year. The figures for 2026 also indicate a specific amount of $69 million in Interest Expense and $64 million in 2025.

Interest Expense encompasses several components, including coupon interest, commitment fees, and the accretion of original issue discounts. Additionally, it includes the amortization of debt premiums, the costs associated with debt issuance, and expenses related to debt modifications or extinguishments. This comprehensive cost structure highlights the various financial obligations that come with managing borrowed funds effectively. Thus, Interest Expense not only reflects the cost of borrowing but also comprises a wide range of expenses directly linked to servicing that debt.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-db98b1c09ec551c8a83f9131498334c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43a8f055527dad4e87136bbd01caf743&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8c3943d4fcccf1ae19651cf71f87bf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa5ffd55eec85058d06665add3afcd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b02dd03910eba2f64d7717819c0ef1bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eddee67b369c229f33b13b2d39309da9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fdce1044a2c44a0e983bbcf60375f53</data>
