<node id="One Big Beautiful Bill Act">
  <data key="d0">One Big Beautiful Bill Act</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The One Big Beautiful Bill Act (OBBBA) is a significant piece of legislation that was enacted into law on July 4, 2025. This act introduces comprehensive changes to the U.S. federal income tax laws, impacting both corporate and individual taxpayers. Among its various provisions, the OBBBA facilitates changes in the realization of corporate alternative minimum tax (CAMT) credits and the valuation of deferred tax assets, which in turn influences tax planning strategies for organizations.

One of the key features of the OBBBA is its tax reform measures, which include the full expensing of domestic research and development costs. Additionally, it increases the investment tax credit for specific investments in domestic semiconductor manufacturing from 25% to 35%. These provisions are aimed at incentivizing domestic production and investment in critical sectors of the economy.

Moreover, the OBBBA implements permanent modifications to the U.S. tax code, significantly impacting how U.S. multinational corporations are taxed. Notably, it allows for immediate expensing of certain costs and alters the taxation framework for foreign profits, which directly affects companies' tax provisions and overall financial strategies. The act, therefore, plays a crucial role in shaping the tax landscape, influencing deductions applicable for U.S. tax purposes and ultimately affecting valuation allowances within organizations.&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act is a legislative measure that impacts corporate tax policy and regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act is legislation that allows for immediate expensing of certain costs and changes the taxation of foreign profits, affecting the company's tax provisions.&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act is a legislative measure that impacts corporate tax policy and regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act is U.S. tax legislation that includes changes to the deductibility of domestic expenses and modifications to the international tax framework.&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act is legislation that impacted the company's tax provisions and Non-GAAP calculations.&lt;SEP&gt;The One Big Beautiful Bill Act was enacted on July 4, 2025, involving significant tax provisions affecting the fiscal environment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-db98b1c09ec551c8a83f9131498334c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-217dcca296bd42c2a1d26c339d20ff32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-528b15deb865d055e3be525ecf5963bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae71f5af8c77cdfb1dcf9e739c3e7b9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7200d8553fd2e4a1586cd2f8af4129fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a296116922ea376dbdc0f563507f5547&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-267e6745b98edf24b0ab1d8c73c24264&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0044cfbed2a6b3917ab79390c074f36&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7de7e1241f8ebf9e1a462ee7b32a55fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fd247a952683a47a5830843ce2924e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fdce1044a2c44a0e983bbcf60375f53</data>
