<node id="Cash and Cash Equivalents">
  <data key="d0">Cash and Cash Equivalents</data>
  <data key="d1">financialmeasure</data>
  <data key="d2">Cash and Cash Equivalents refer to the liquid assets held by a company that can be quickly converted into cash. As of January 25, 2026, Cash and Cash Equivalents were reported to be $10,605 million. This category is an essential part of total cash holdings, which also include cash equivalents and restricted cash, with amounts of $7,218 million and $6,264 million specified, indicating various components of the company's liquidity.

Notably, Cash and Cash Equivalents experienced a significant increase prior to the January 2026 figure, rising to $16,178 million as of November 2, 2025. This increase suggests robust liquidity management within the company. In another assessment, Cash and Cash Equivalents were recorded at $14,174 million at the end of a fiscal quarter, highlighting fluctuations in liquid asset totals over time.

Overall, Cash and Cash Equivalents serve as a critical indicator of the company's short-term financial health, representing available funds and the ability to meet immediate obligations through these liquid assets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-db98b1c09ec551c8a83f9131498334c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b33403642cf163673735a8236b77616c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6914852673b586e472efa313d90a7cbf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa5ffd55eec85058d06665add3afcd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e0837ab88a60a72e576353a5fe0398b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf438b7e4564db1875e01c22f58140c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4f3a99d3019490d0bf692c1a4227a55</data>
