<node id="Revenue">
  <data key="d0">Revenue</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Revenue is a financial metric that quantifies the income generated by a company's business operations, primarily derived from the sales of products, subscriptions, and services. For the fiscal year 2026, Revenue reached $215.9 billion, reflecting a remarkable 65% increase from the previous year.

In more specific figures, Revenue was recorded at $7,012 in 2026 and $7,166 in 2025, with a total increase in revenue noted from $7,003.1 million in 2024 to $9,005.7 million in 2025, which represented a significant 28.6% rise. The total revenue for the year ended December 31, 2024, was $7,003.1 million, marking a 19.5% increase from 2023.

Overall, Revenue serves as a crucial indicator of a company's financial health and business success, emphasizing the importance of operational performance and sales effectiveness.&lt;SEP&gt;Revenue is the income generated from the sale of products, the timing of which is affected by various factors and is difficult to forecast.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fe1fafd9b0c6f09af84ad373757a9b00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43a8f055527dad4e87136bbd01caf743&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cef59817c38511355f56938f73f6db2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8b46fa35ec37b9bd74df50bd6a347ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ade0a30743a7edf4b6eaaebdf38aaaa2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6da69316e8a6a8b2389b44396109382&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c17cee8b5d4c0058ad449ca8d769b9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bbc7bb48e6d4943b055b0203ce8adb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6837c4686c704cf481e701435fa08a62&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-daa7b8544edadd0f701ab9d8efd26b8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b60e0f97fb25eebd70430165e6231145</data>
