<node id="Revenue Recognition">
  <data key="d0">Revenue Recognition</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The process of recording revenue, which includes establishing allowances for sales returns and accruing for customer programs.&lt;SEP&gt;Revenue Recognition is the company's policy for recognizing revenue from sales, which involves the transfer of control of goods or services to the customer and the allocation of transaction prices.&lt;SEP&gt;Revenue recognition involves accounting for a contract with a customer when certain conditions are met, including the transfer of control of a promised product or service to a customer.&lt;SEP&gt;Revenue recognition involves accounting for a contract with a customer when certain conditions are met, including the transfer of control of a promised product or service to a customer.&lt;SEP&gt;Revenue Recognition is the timing of when the company recognizes revenue from a sale, which is affected by many factors and is difficult to forecast, impacting the company's financial planning.&lt;SEP&gt;Revenue Recognition pertains to how revenue is recognized from contracts with customers involving multiple performance obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3f2ce3a4f3492cdc62d91339c8332500&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0f7533f1c0231555ac5ae30f4d37842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b02dd03910eba2f64d7717819c0ef1bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99ce04c1c520fc4abd8bec8e5e164c28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c9d9262cc591e5a663ff1343e1ab5b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6837c4686c704cf481e701435fa08a62&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1442e3c91c8552eddf70d0f36cf38e91</data>
