<node id="Board of Directors">
  <data key="d0">Board of Directors</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Board of Directors serves as a pivotal governing body within corporations, comprised of individuals elected by shareholders to oversee management and make substantial strategic decisions. This board holds ultimate authority over key matters such as the declaration and payment of dividends, approval of stock repurchase programs, and other essential corporate actions that impact financial management. Its primary responsibility is to ensure that all decisions are in alignment with the best interests of shareholders while simultaneously considering the company’s overall financial health.

In its financial governance role, the Board of Directors evaluates major corporate risks, including challenges like cybersecurity threats, and assesses the fair value of share-based awards. Notably, the Board authorized a stock repurchase program for AVGO in the second quarter of fiscal year 2025, reflecting its proactive engagement in financial strategies. The Board acts as a representative body for all shareholders, integrating their interests into corporate governance to ensure equitable decision-making.

The responsibilities of the Board of Directors extend beyond financial oversight; they also conduct elections, oversee organizational activities, and ensure compliance with relevant laws and regulations. The influence of larger corporate entities, such as SoftBank Group, can significantly shape the Board's decision-making processes and policies. This dynamic underscores the foundational role of the Board of Directors in guiding corporate governance and enhancing corporate performance while fulfilling shareholder interests.

Moreover, the Board of Directors has authorized stock repurchase programs for KLAC, with a notable substantial increase approved in fiscal 2024, indicating their active governance over financial decisions. Similarly, the Board has affirmed its role in sanctioning stock repurchase programs for ANET. Collectively, these actions exemplify the Board's authoritative position in overseeing critical financial strategies and maintaining organizational accountability across different companies.&lt;SEP&gt;The Board of Directors is the governing body of ANET that authorizes stock repurchase programs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a36df99dfa3a16bd8e4d429df7cf42a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-625ca1cf50e3b24380c8601c96bdd7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f533007cd8f65f3f88984fedd522d05d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1fc03c6340e9f91435287101b7ba57e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f60be1d369008dda0461cefaf2ff61fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4845686f7704c5c80e402305d19f7ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77d86694dce1fc1e9c3d3ac3bab4c5be&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01ee832930ff813d9db8fa5bfa02507e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0875cdce54018cd923f6cab7e6b6692&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a23fd7a348fc3f448641e9ef7d5be33a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d780eacfb91e291d22055bf3aca31fa3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-541097656a29c150756d08c4943ad8b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e0837ab88a60a72e576353a5fe0398b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20ff684928510a0aa4726b57cf95bfc6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1d26aff29032e66965549a44d8a5643&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db16028b865589c8deb5630190c22030&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0d1065649bee800c972122f59f7fc8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2d39980a89a2b136f0a1d2d58d59c86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12e1f77fe538051f6128dd4bc89f0c38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9cf777435ca6135f2543fc921d450ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf1bb802539f8961349a60bf6c9b66c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab4fed2451ba98a9b8f9ac6037703d67&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0292dbc49bc4382dc3bccb8e9b403c95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e87a4f351685e936b673b5d8beb0687a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e31bb121b1f8d055ee99592a3cbb3ab5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a607ffbfac50d0f1129f1e67cb61a773&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6c2882daa1ec6a56270d1197f7a79d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af924d24274505e948110654fd090f0c</data>
