  <data key="d0">Cash Dividends</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cash dividends are financial transactions where the company pays out cash to its shareholders.&lt;SEP&gt;Cash Dividends refer to the total amounts of regular quarterly cash dividends and dividend equivalents paid to shareholders.&lt;SEP&gt;Cash dividends are payments made by a corporation to its shareholders.&lt;SEP&gt;Cash dividends are payments made to shareholders, which are not guaranteed to be declared consistently.&lt;SEP&gt;Cash dividends are payments made to shareholders, declared by the Board of Directors and subject to approval.&lt;SEP&gt;Cash dividends are payments made to shareholders, which are not guaranteed to be declared consistently.&lt;SEP&gt;Cash dividends are payments made to shareholders, declared by the Board of Directors and subject to approval.</data>
