<node id="OEMs">
  <data key="d0">OEMs</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">OEMs are direct customers of NVIDIA, producing products that incorporate NVIDIA's technology.&lt;SEP&gt;OEMs, or Original Equipment Manufacturers, are companies that produce parts used in products manufactured by other companies.&lt;SEP&gt;OEMs refer to Original Equipment Manufacturers that utilize the company's products in chips and end products they sell, particularly in the PRC market.&lt;SEP&gt;OEMs refers to Original Equipment Manufacturers, entities that may increasingly develop their own technology or use competitors' technology in their devices due to various factors including government policies.&lt;SEP&gt;OEMs, or Original Equipment Manufacturers, are companies that produce parts used in products manufactured by other companies.&lt;SEP&gt;OEMs refer to Original Equipment Manufacturers that utilize the company's products in chips and end products they sell, particularly in the PRC market.&lt;SEP&gt;OEMs refers to Original Equipment Manufacturers, entities that may increasingly develop their own technology or use competitors' technology in their devices due to various factors including government policies.</data>
