  <data key="d0">Blackwell Full-Scale Datacenter Solutions</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Blackwell full-scale datacenter solutions represent a new product line from NVIDIA, contributing to a change in their business model and affecting gross margins.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777252931</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gross Profit">
  <data key="d0">Gross Profit</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Gross profit is a financial metric representing total net revenue less the cost of revenue, which decreased from 75.0% to 71.1% for NVIDIA in fiscal year 2026.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross Profit is the profit after deducting the cost of goods sold from revenue, amounting to $3,435 in 2026 and $3,496 in 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross profit for the year ended December 31, 2024, was $4,491.3 million, a 23.7% increase from the previous year.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross profit is a financial metric that represents the profit a company makes after deducting the costs associated with producing and selling its products, which increased to $5,768.7 million in 2025, up by 28.4% from $4,491.3 million in 2024.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43a8f055527dad4e87136bbd01caf743&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c17cee8b5d4c0058ad449ca8d769b9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bbc7bb48e6d4943b055b0203ce8adb4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777381819</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gross Margin">
  <data key="d0">Gross Margin</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Gross Margin is a crucial financial metric that represents the percentage of revenue remaining after deducting the cost of goods sold (COGS) or costs of revenues. It serves as an indicator of a company’s profitability and efficiency in managing its production and service costs. Gross margin fluctuates based on several factors, including revenue levels, product mix, and variations in manufacturing and servicing costs.

For NVIDIA, gross margin experienced a decline from 75.0% to 71.1% in fiscal year 2026. This decrease was attributed to a significant change in the company's business model and a substantial charge related to H20 inventory. In contrast, there were improvements noted in earlier fiscal years. Specifically, gross margin rose from 61.9% in 2023 to 64.1% in 2024, demonstrating enhanced product margins. For the year ended December 31, 2024, the gross margin was reported at 64.1%, which was slightly up from 61.9% in the previous year, and it remained constant at this level through December 31, 2025.

Overall, gross margin showcases essential insights into a company’s capacity to scale its operations efficiently while managing costs effectively. Variations in gross margin reflect both the challenges and opportunities that a company faces as it adapts its business strategies and product offerings to the market demands.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe1fafd9b0c6f09af84ad373757a9b00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2b01ab4070bbe76a7dd3d4ffb383d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0f7533f1c0231555ac5ae30f4d37842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e28f2689bd6a5fe65b47f7c31f1a8adc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99ce04c1c520fc4abd8bec8e5e164c28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7df88c2c7b38c5eb12580560b4e0dc2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-923b6a774533b6ee182ac5d5b97611cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c17cee8b5d4c0058ad449ca8d769b9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bbc7bb48e6d4943b055b0203ce8adb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69f1af12f4eafcde14c51426aec9aa50</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777381841</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fiscal Year 2026">
  <data key="d0">Fiscal Year 2026</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Fiscal Year 2026 is the most recent fiscal year for which NVIDIA reported financial data, including a decrease in gross margins and revenue growth in specific segments.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2026 is a period during which the company spent $6.1 billion on capital expenditures.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2026 is the financial year starting on or after July 1, 2025, and ending on or before June 30, 2026, relevant for the implementation of new accounting standards.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2026 refers to the financial year being discussed in the context of revenue guidance and operational results.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2026 refers to the financial year that includes the first quarter being reported and involves Broadcom's performance metrics.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91ba0c40d4695fe5428e9f1aaee99693&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-528b15deb865d055e3be525ecf5963bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf438b7e4564db1875e01c22f58140c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bba57ca7db1179105f2714d5fa2f79b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777380948</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fiscal Year 2025">
  <data key="d0">Fiscal Year 2025</data>
  <data key="d1">timeperiod</data>
  <data key="d2">Fiscal Year 2025 refers to a specific financial period that ended on June 30, 2025. This year is notable for NVIDIA, as it serves as the previous fiscal year for which the company reported financial data, providing a comparative period for the analysis of revenue and expenses. During this time, NVIDIA reported a significant 24% increase in total revenues, reflecting improved financial performance despite challenges posed by tariffs.

In Fiscal Year 2025, NVIDIA allocated $3.4 billion toward capital expenditures, indicating substantial investment in growth initiatives. The company's sales to distributors were also a critical aspect, contributing 48% of the net revenue during this period. Furthermore, it was a year marked by a decrease in the provision for income taxes due to tax incentives, which reduced the tax burden by approximately $2,709 million.

Additionally, key financial activities recorded during Fiscal Year 2025 included research and development expenses, along with detailed operational, investing, and financing activities. This period also highlighted specific wafer production and materials purchasing data, showcasing the operational aspects of the company’s performance. Overall, Fiscal Year 2025 was a pivotal year for NVIDIA, characterized by significant financial growth and strategic expenditures.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2025 is the following accounting period that includes details regarding operating, investing, and financing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2025 is the financial year during which sales to distributors accounted for 48% of net revenue.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2025 is the financial year referenced in which specific wafer production and materials purchasing data is highlighted.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2025 refers to the financial year during which tax incentives decreased the provision for income taxes by approximately $2,709 million.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91ba0c40d4695fe5428e9f1aaee99693&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cef59817c38511355f56938f73f6db2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0f7533f1c0231555ac5ae30f4d37842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8c3943d4fcccf1ae19651cf71f87bf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20ff684928510a0aa4726b57cf95bfc6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9046829702051c016224dd2ad2934dd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb9c473a56337b1bb1aca06b15d0259d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ffb6ca21b9e1992311d5ea2722c2f55</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777380518</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
