  <data key="d2">Operating expenses increased due to higher compensation and benefits expenses resulting from employee growth.&lt;SEP&gt;Operating Expenses include all expenses involved in the operations of a company, totaling $1,604 in 2026 and $1,321 in 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Operating expenses are the costs incurred by the company in its regular business activities, excluding capital expenditures.&lt;SEP&gt;Operating expenses are the costs incurred by the company in its regular business activities, excluding capital expenditures.&lt;SEP&gt;Operating expenses include research and development, sales and marketing, and general and administrative expenses, which increased by $365.9 million, or 23.7%, for the year ended December 31, 2025 compared to 2024.&lt;SEP&gt;Operating expenses consist of costs incurred during regular business operations, affecting profitability and financial health.</data>
