<node id="Income Taxes">
  <data key="d0">Income Taxes</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3f2ce3a4f3492cdc62d91339c8332500&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f659a7f219f7f617d5e8dc482fab75d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e0837ab88a60a72e576353a5fe0398b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0044cfbed2a6b3917ab79390c074f36&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa412cb5c38ae9e212cc41c77cb5b6bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2bcf7035b2263b22ce2270c9abedd363&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c17cee8b5d4c0058ad449ca8d769b9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c9d9262cc591e5a663ff1343e1ab5b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5e7cc3c7c57e107c4d688872735f76a</data>
  <data key="d2">Income Taxes refer to the taxes imposed on a company's income, including both mandatory payments made to the government based on earnings and the complexities surrounding tax laws and regulations. These payments are subject to various factors that can influence their volatility and are calculated in accordance with Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP). 

In the context of financial reporting, Income Taxes include Deferred Tax Assets and Liabilities, which arise in both U.S. and foreign jurisdictions. The asset and liability method is employed when accounting for these taxes, reflecting the tax liabilities incurred by the entity. Moreover, these tax liabilities can be represented with both positive and negative values, indicating the potential for future tax benefits or obligations.

Income Taxes thus encompass a comprehensive framework of responsibilities that a company has toward taxation, which can vary across different regions. This variability includes specific considerations under the tax regimes of the United Kingdom and other foreign jurisdictions, demonstrating that companies operate within a complex system of international tax legislation.&lt;SEP&gt;Income Taxes are a concept referring to the taxes that the company must pay to the U.S. and foreign jurisdictions based on its income.</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777381820</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deferred Tax Assets">
  <data key="d0">Deferred Tax Assets</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3f2ce3a4f3492cdc62d91339c8332500&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-528b15deb865d055e3be525ecf5963bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae71f5af8c77cdfb1dcf9e739c3e7b9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-737963f5a4aa4c7ac5ff75bd66cabe60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7df88c2c7b38c5eb12580560b4e0dc2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2bcf7035b2263b22ce2270c9abedd363&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42aa9c7f7d4ca12621cf2af559e1aa29</data>
  <data key="d2">The Valuation Allowance is used to reduce the Deferred Tax Assets to the amount more likely to be realized.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred tax assets are financial figures representing the tax benefits of future deductions that are recognized in accounting due to temporary differences between book income and taxable income.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred Tax Assets are recognized for the estimated future tax effects of temporary differences and for net operating loss and tax credit carryovers.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred tax assets are a financial consideration for AMD, which may be realized or result in tax liabilities.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred Tax Assets are determined based on temporary differences between financial reporting and tax bases of assets and liabilities.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred tax assets are amounts of tax benefits and credits that can be used to reduce future tax liabilities.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred Tax Assets are a concept in accounting that represents the tax benefits that can be utilized in the future against taxable income. They require valuation allowances to be assessed for potential impairment.</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777381820</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
