  <data key="d2">Non-Marketable Equity Securities are part of the company's investments in private companies.&lt;SEP&gt;Investments are financial commitments that can impact AMD's business.&lt;SEP&gt;Investments are the financial instruments or companies the company may acquire from time to time.&lt;SEP&gt;Investments are capital allocations to enhance business operations or capabilities, often linked to higher returns but accompanied by risks associated with market conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Investments are the financial instruments or companies the company may acquire from time to time.&lt;SEP&gt;Investments are capital allocations to enhance business operations or capabilities, often linked to higher returns but accompanied by risks associated with market conditions.</data>
