<node id="Fiscal 2025">
  <data key="d0">Fiscal 2025</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Fiscal 2025 is a significant financial year encompassing various key aspects of a company's performance and strategic decisions. During this fiscal period, the organization reported its net revenue, gross margin, operating income, operating margin, net income, and earnings per diluted share, providing a comprehensive overview of its financial health. 

In this year, the organization took noteworthy actions, including recording a full valuation allowance against the CAMT credit deferred tax asset, which impacted its effective tax rate and the provision for income taxes. Additionally, Applied Materials, Inc. announced a workforce reduction plan and entered new tax incentive agreements in Singapore, indicating changes in workforce management and strategic positioning in international markets.

Fiscal 2025 also saw the company identifying goodwill impairment charges in the PCB and Component Inspection reportable segment, alongside an assessment of tangible and purchased intangible assets for impairment. This reflects a careful evaluation of the company's asset values and potential risks.

The year is characterized by a detailed analysis of operating margins and interest expenses, as well as providing insight into revenue recognition, product sales, and overall financial performance compared to previous fiscal periods. The current financial year is also the focus of scrutiny regarding provisions for income taxes and cash flow analysis, highlighting its importance in the broader context of financial reporting and performance evaluation.

Moreover, Fiscal 2025 emphasizes substantial acquisitions of intangible assets, further shaping the company’s investment and growth trajectory during this period. Overall, this fiscal year is critical for understanding the organization's financial strategies, operational efficiency, and long-term viability in the market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e7481c513c84b894dbf5566a03c9c31d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7200d8553fd2e4a1586cd2f8af4129fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a29194982b15aafff922b31789e91ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1329332311e82d0b2cc6f7232bfaa092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed2b32ad29a09feed46df0c963169feb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71dff42efadaa177f60791628d62844c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d1a6abe12ff0346c565b00be1a824f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5e7cc3c7c57e107c4d688872735f76a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fdce1044a2c44a0e983bbcf60375f53&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0644a249b2d47b7e49a78f4bf359cb71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa0903de4275b3766162843253dfdcd3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777382524</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fiscal 2024">
  <data key="d0">Fiscal 2024</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Fiscal 2024 is a significant financial period for the company, marking the time in which key metrics such as net revenue, gross margin, operating income, operating margin, net income, and earnings per diluted share were reported. This period is crucial for evaluating the company's overall performance and its financial health, establishing benchmarks for subsequent analysis.

During Fiscal 2024, the company recognized an impairment indicator within the PCB and Component Inspection reportable segment, which led to goodwill impairment charges. This situation indicates challenges faced during this fiscal year that had noteworthy implications for the company's financial standing.

Furthermore, Fiscal 2024 is the financial year that directly precedes Fiscal 2025, providing a comparative basis for analyzing revenue growth and evaluating changes in operating results. As such, it serves as a critical reference point for measuring progress and understanding trends in the company's financial trajectory.

Additionally, Fiscal 2024 is utilized as a prior financial reporting period, which acts as a benchmarking tool for performance assessment. It is also the year for which the provision for income taxes was assessed, highlighting its importance in the context of taxation and regulatory compliance. Overall, the period is pivotal for both operational decision-making and financial analysis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e7481c513c84b894dbf5566a03c9c31d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1329332311e82d0b2cc6f7232bfaa092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e28f2689bd6a5fe65b47f7c31f1a8adc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed2b32ad29a09feed46df0c963169feb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71dff42efadaa177f60791628d62844c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d1a6abe12ff0346c565b00be1a824f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fdce1044a2c44a0e983bbcf60375f53&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0644a249b2d47b7e49a78f4bf359cb71</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
