<node id="Korea">
  <data key="d0">Korea</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Korea is a geographic region that contributed to the net revenue of the company, with a 20% share in 2025.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a country where the company has substantial business operations and customer base.&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a significant market for the business and part of the geographical concentration of the customer base.&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a region contributing to the company's revenues, with 12%, 9%, and 18% of total revenues in fiscal years 2025, 2024, and 2023, respectively.&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a geographic region mentioned as a source of semiconductor manufacturers investing in China.&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a region contributing to the company's revenues, though with a smaller percentage compared to China and Taiwan.&lt;SEP&gt;Korea is a location that contributes to the total revenues, with a percentage of total revenues during the specified periods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85c73190292489fe36964fdd5fc32b0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b0f36135b3b08cac0302bf342d7918d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d8ee469fd420dd945b64b580faff532&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2b01ab4070bbe76a7dd3d4ffb383d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b7969877a8fd0841863c700fea233da5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1329332311e82d0b2cc6f7232bfaa092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db3fcbe26ec52d22abad5f9f0435fea6</data>
