<node id="U.S. CHIPS and Science Act">
  <data key="d0">U.S. CHIPS and Science Act</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The U.S. CHIPS and Science Act, enacted on August 9, 2022, creates a 25% investment tax credit for certain investments in domestic semiconductor manufacturing, reducing current and future income taxes payable by $233 million and $548 million respectively.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-217dcca296bd42c2a1d26c339d20ff32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777259232</data>
