<node id="Singapore">
  <data key="d0">Singapore</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Singapore is a country that serves as an important jurisdiction for business operations, particularly for corporations like Applied Materials, Inc. This country has been granted additional conditional reduced tax rates that will expire beginning in fiscal 2030. These tax incentives have a significant impact on companies' income tax provisions and profitability, especially as Singapore is one of the foreign jurisdictions where these companies earn a majority of their non-U.S. profits.

Additionally, Singapore is recognized for providing various tax incentives through its Economic Development Board, making it an attractive location for significant manufacturing operations. As a foreign jurisdiction, it is also subject to tax rates that may change, which is a critical consideration for companies operating within its borders. Overall, Singapore's favorable tax environment and status as a key hub for business operations have positioned it as a critical player in the global market for companies seeking to optimize their fiscal strategies.&lt;SEP&gt;Singapore is a Southeast Asian country that hosts some manufacturing facilities relevant to the business.&lt;SEP&gt;Singapore is a country where the company benefits from tax incentives provided by the Singapore Economic Development Board.&lt;SEP&gt;Singapore is a Southeast Asian country that hosts some manufacturing facilities relevant to the business.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-217dcca296bd42c2a1d26c339d20ff32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f659a7f219f7f617d5e8dc482fab75d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7200d8553fd2e4a1586cd2f8af4129fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a29194982b15aafff922b31789e91ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6295c9841b489759670dace2137e3d9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f20aa9a81d6ab585196c52c4b81c36f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a296116922ea376dbdc0f563507f5547&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b02dd03910eba2f64d7717819c0ef1bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a34feb04cdff823a759d00077b835348</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777380517</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="U.S. Government">
  <data key="d0">U.S. Government</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The U.S. Government plays a pivotal role in shaping both domestic and international economic landscapes through various legislative and regulatory actions. It is responsible for enacting key pieces of legislation, including the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, the U.S. CHIPS and Science Act, and the One Big Beautiful Bill Act, which reflect its influence over fiscal policy and economic strategy.

In addition to legislation, the U.S. Government formulates and implements trade policies and export regulations that significantly impact businesses and their operations. This includes the granting of export licenses, the imposition of tariffs, and the establishment of regulations that govern international trade. Such regulations not only dictate how companies conduct their businesses but also have the potential to alter their financial results and operational capabilities.

The U.S. Government's regulatory framework is crucial in guiding domestic businesses and ensuring compliance with international standards. By establishing comprehensive policies that affect both local and global markets, the U.S. Government directly influences the economic environment in which organizations operate.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. Government is involved in semiconductor funding policies and transactions, impacting companies like Intel.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. Government is mentioned as a significant entity acquiring equity interests and influencing financial agreements, such as the CHIPS Act agreement.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. government is responsible for enacting tariffs and trade policies that affect the import of various items.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. government is the public institution responsible for creating and enforcing laws and policies, which can impact the economy.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. government has enacted trade restrictions affecting the export of products, particularly related to semiconductors and technology.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. Government issues export controls and regulations affecting the export of certain technologies and products.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-217dcca296bd42c2a1d26c339d20ff32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85c73190292489fe36964fdd5fc32b0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0f7533f1c0231555ac5ae30f4d37842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d780eacfb91e291d22055bf3aca31fa3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bea44a78e2f296bf07e25ff7ce0f0dc0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6aeca2a51a3e2732d9a306c9c0622909&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ab89f3ce951ee013c683ef4d703a4a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57e076aea89251dd867c3c67f96d95af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28ad4cf0cdd97b38006d5c4b661a0eaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48398f86ee66960c2b40a409c49e55e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ca4353a43bcb8671d00174ee0da3be0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec5ba923d7a24c9eaf76ee9457a79656</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777382060</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
