<node id="Israel">
  <data key="d0">Israel</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Israel is a significant geographic region where AMAT conducts product development and manufacturing activities. It serves as a primary location for the company’s operations, contributing notably to its revenues and hosting a leading-edge fabrication facility along with several product development centers. Despite its importance, Israel faces notable geopolitical challenges, including regional tensions and conflicts that may affect operational stability.

The manufacturing sector in Israel is characterized by significant operations, but it has also encountered difficulties, such as stalled or canceled construction projects. These disruptions apply to projects by major companies, including Intel Foundry, which has also faced delays in its activities within Israel. 

Moreover, Israel is identified as a jurisdiction where AMAT generates a substantial portion of its non-U.S. profits. However, this comes with a caveat, as the tax rates applicable in Israel may fluctuate, impacting the company's financial landscape. Overall, the dual nature of Israel as both a critical operational hub and a location susceptible to external geopolitical factors illustrates the complex environment in which AMAT operates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26fa1d1070f941c3c83605779a2af8f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6295c9841b489759670dace2137e3d9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f20aa9a81d6ab585196c52c4b81c36f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a296116922ea376dbdc0f563507f5547&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db3fcbe26ec52d22abad5f9f0435fea6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-433658da14495378bbd17c93b4779dda&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-401a34b148ef0ff9e9be44cd80f4dd57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f6b26aa2f7f768941f9a0f229275f9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88f2b4d088361dd806e394a19506ee8f</data>
