  <data key="d0">Accounts Receivable</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Accounts Receivable represents the money owed to the company for goods or services provided, which the company has sold on credit.&lt;SEP&gt;Accounts Receivable are the amounts due from customers for products and services provided, impacting the company's cash inflows.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88fbdee009d132142f267759b80b8fcd</data>
