<node id="Senior Notes">
  <data key="d0">Senior Notes</data>
  <data key="d1">financialinstrument</data>
  <data key="d2">Senior Notes are a type of debt obligation issued by a company, representing an aggregate principal amount of unsecured debt with varying due dates as detailed in the company's financial statements. They have a higher claim on assets in the event of bankruptcy and are part of the company's financing activities. These debt instruments have varying maturity dates ranging from fiscal year 2029 to fiscal year 2063, and the entity has an aggregate principal debt obligation on them. Senior Notes are also related to the company's capital structure and indebtedness, with an outstanding indebtedness of $5.95 billion consisting of unsecured long-term notes. In certain conditions, such as rating downgrades, the company may be required to repurchase these financial instruments. An example of a Senior Note issuance is the $750.0 million in February 2024. Overall, Senior Notes are senior, unsecured notes with an aggregate principal amount of $5.95 billion.&lt;SEP&gt;Senior Notes refer to a financial instrument issued amounting to $2.5 billion, with different maturities and terms specified.&lt;SEP&gt;The Senior Notes are debt securities issued by the organization with specific terms and conditions, including interest rates and maturity dates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfac3dde6482c2f8fd9ea0e0c659c15b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb113ac9e0cc9e74e5cc817ec0cd9a79&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e39760d10a53b7326a952678788b4f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cb9583c9766314f3cbadb2fe74821b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d34b219513d1d4953f831b7693287834&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcbd467e0d3d2d1e90e50929e4ef4372&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa5ffd55eec85058d06665add3afcd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ff8c5ead4252ae2a31532cc82caa936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fdce1044a2c44a0e983bbcf60375f53</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777382510</data>
