<node id="Effective Tax Rate">
  <data key="d0">Effective Tax Rate</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa5ffd55eec85058d06665add3afcd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8324363f0a048e57166b3353e15ed038&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c17cee8b5d4c0058ad449ca8d769b9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69f1af12f4eafcde14c51426aec9aa50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0644a249b2d47b7e49a78f4bf359cb71</data>
  <data key="d2">The effective tax rate for fiscal 2025 was higher than the prior fiscal year primarily due to a remeasurement of deferred tax assets resulting from new tax incentive agreements in Singapore.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;The effective tax rate is the ratio of the actual taxes paid for a period to the pre-tax income for the same period.&lt;SEP&gt;The ratio of income tax expense to income before taxes.&lt;SEP&gt;The effective tax rate is the average rate at which an entity's income is taxed, influenced by various factors including tax regimes.&lt;SEP&gt;The effective tax rate for the year ended December 31, 2025, was 17.4%, an increase from 12.6% in the previous year.&lt;SEP&gt;The effective tax rate decreased from 13.8% in 2023 to 12.6% in 2024.&lt;SEP&gt;Effective tax rate indicates the average rate at which an entity is taxed, significant for financial reporting.</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777382511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
