<node id="Provision for Income Taxes">
  <data key="d0">Provision for Income Taxes</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43a8f055527dad4e87136bbd01caf743&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8c3943d4fcccf1ae19651cf71f87bf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa5ffd55eec85058d06665add3afcd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b02dd03910eba2f64d7717819c0ef1bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eddee67b369c229f33b13b2d39309da9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c17cee8b5d4c0058ad449ca8d769b9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69f1af12f4eafcde14c51426aec9aa50</data>
  <data key="d2">The Provision for Income Taxes refers to the amount set aside by a company to cover its income tax obligations. This provision is a significant component of the company's financial statements, with detailed accounting for the years 2025, 2024, and 2023. For the fiscal year ending December 31, 2025, the provision for income taxes was recorded at $738.3 million, marking an increase of 78.8% compared to the prior year. This rise in provision was partly offset by a decrease in the effective tax rate.

The Provision for Income Taxes is influenced by various factors, including the geographical composition of pre-tax income, which comprises jurisdictions with differing tax rates. As such, the company’s tax obligations are shaped by where its income is generated and the tax incentives available in those locations. Notably, there are tax incentives provided in various jurisdictions aimed at promoting investment and employment, which can positively impact the overall provision.

Additionally, the provision reflects an estimate of income taxes based on both current and deferred tax liabilities. For the years 2026 and 2025, specific amounts are forecasted, with provisions indicated at $302 million and $934 million, respectively. Overall, the Provision for Income Taxes serves as a critical financial measure, representing the expected tax burden of a company for a given fiscal period.</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777381858</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
