<node id="Strategic Investments">
  <data key="d0">Strategic Investments</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Strategic Investments are investments made to achieve specific business objectives, which may fail to commercialize technologies.&lt;SEP&gt;Strategic Investments are investments made in companies, technologies, or products to achieve specific business objectives, which can lead to risks such as diversion of management's attention and disruption of ongoing businesses.&lt;SEP&gt;Strategic Investments are investments made by Applied Materials, Inc. that result in realized and unrealized gains or losses, impacting the company's net income.&lt;SEP&gt;Strategic investments are external growth strategies that Arm makes, which come with risks associated with managing the growth effectively.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-99b76900a97d7c959bc5ca885c3601da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a29194982b15aafff922b31789e91ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a09335734e89edd5d8f3e04bd3466cd8</data>
