<node id="Tariffs">
  <data key="d0">Tariffs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Tariffs are taxes imposed on imported goods, which can affect the cost and competitiveness of products.&lt;SEP&gt;Tariffs are taxes imposed on imported goods, which can disrupt international trade relationships and affect businesses.&lt;SEP&gt;Tariffs are taxes imposed on imports, which the U.S. administration increased, affecting international trade dynamics.&lt;SEP&gt;Tariffs are taxes imposed on imported goods, which can disrupt international trade relationships and affect businesses.&lt;SEP&gt;Tariffs are taxes imposed on imports, which the U.S. administration increased, affecting international trade dynamics.&lt;SEP&gt;Tariffs are taxes imposed on goods as they cross international borders, which can affect costs and pricing.&lt;SEP&gt;Tariffs are taxes imposed on imported or exported goods and can affect the cost and profitability of manufacturing operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-85c73190292489fe36964fdd5fc32b0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-050055b3bc468fa0d183c4f69822f018&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5776951d5c25cce5d7ce7eb72c02bd77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca05e43c085b4801092259d8bb642b30&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ca4353a43bcb8671d00174ee0da3be0</data>
