  <data key="d0">U.S. Department of Commerce</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The U.S. Department of Commerce is a government entity that sets and enforces export control regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. Department of Commerce is a federal department that oversees the Bureau of Industry and Security and is involved in export control regulations.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. Department of Commerce is responsible for implementing and enforcing regulations such as the BIS Rules.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. Department of Commerce is a federal department overseeing various economic and trade-related matters, including the Bureau of Industry and Security.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. Department of Commerce regulates export restrictions impacting the organization's operations.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. Department of Commerce regulates export restrictions impacting the organization's operations.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.S. Department of Commerce (DOC) is mentioned as being contractually bound by the CHIPS Act agreement.</data>
