<node id="Deferred Income Taxes">
  <data key="d0">Deferred Income Taxes</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Deferred Income Taxes represent taxes payable in future periods, amounting to a net change of -$78 in 2026 and $668 in 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred Income Taxes are taxes that are accounted for in future periods due to temporary differences between financial statement carrying amounts and tax basis of assets and liabilities.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred Income Taxes represent the temporary differences between tax deductions and income recognition for financial reporting purposes, impacting the company's cash flows.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred Income Taxes is a financial data point that represents temporary differences between tax deductions and the reporting of expenses or income for financial statement purposes.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred Income Taxes represent the temporary difference between the tax base of assets or liabilities and their carrying amount in the financial statements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-43a8f055527dad4e87136bbd01caf743&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88fbdee009d132142f267759b80b8fcd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42aa9c7f7d4ca12621cf2af559e1aa29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2201ee5164eca6f8a4fed098d64357e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f683649d33f58f1759bf7001deddc60</data>
