<node id="GAAP">
  <data key="d0">GAAP</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Generally Accepted Accounting Principles, commonly referred to as GAAP, is a set of accounting standards and guidelines utilized for financial reporting. GAAP serves as a standardized framework for financial accounting practices primarily in the United States. It encompasses a series of rules and principles designed to ensure consistency and transparency in financial reporting.

The purpose of GAAP is to provide a consistent methodology for financial calculations and reporting, which aids businesses in presenting their financial results in a clear and comparable manner. Companies, including Applied Materials, Inc., rely on GAAP to guide their accounting practices, covering various aspects such as deferred taxes and income tax provisions.

Additionally, GAAP is instrumental in establishing the groundwork for accounting practices, helping to standardize reporting across different organizations and sectors within the U.S. It ensures that financial statements are prepared in accordance with accepted rules and guidelines, facilitating understanding and comparability for investors, regulators, and other stakeholders.&lt;SEP&gt;GAAP refers to Generally Accepted Accounting Principles, which are a set of accounting standards that companies use to prepare their financial statements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-531a2d4da0efcbaa075b41456e2d3536&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1e351045874ef4f72c98449caf3e612&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28d0d279e198946ca35e2e93f3701350&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf438b7e4564db1875e01c22f58140c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b38febc44090948b4632a44869ab7045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c21ae3c35debcd28aecb74f55451ec4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777382155</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Non-GAAP">
  <data key="d0">Non-GAAP</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Non-GAAP refers to financial measures that exclude certain items from the financial statements that are prepared in accordance with GAAP.&lt;SEP&gt;Non-GAAP refers to financial metrics that exclude certain costs or expenses to give a clearer view of operational performance.</data>
