<node id="quarterly_mda">
  <data key="d0">quarterly_mda</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Quarterly MDA, or Management's Discussion and Analysis, is a type of document that contains financial information for a specific quarter. It is issued quarterly by companies, such as AMD, and provides a discussion of the company's financial performance. The document is an essential section in a company's financial report, offering insights into the company's operations, financial condition, and future prospects. It is designed to provide investors and other stakeholders with a comprehensive understanding of the company's financial health and strategic direction.&lt;SEP&gt;quarterly_mda stands for the company's quarterly management's discussion and analysis.&lt;SEP&gt;quarterly_mda refers to the type of document, which is a management discussion and analysis report for a quarterly period.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bde81dfa7c0130867695a7023e89cf63&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0a83ce1ab52e2df80576ef179eeec72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42b87cf93df46f504c0e370bbcbc6d94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54b2dd7afb5853f7b9fcb8fff6544b20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f60be1d369008dda0461cefaf2ff61fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4845686f7704c5c80e402305d19f7ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77d86694dce1fc1e9c3d3ac3bab4c5be&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6430e92774e5a3f258ef2544910d4dd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af924d24274505e948110654fd090f0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41d8e02bddab5bcdf259b2f8e2f6a009</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777382168</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Repurchase Program">
  <data key="d0">Repurchase Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Repurchase Program is an authorization for AMD to repurchase up to $12 billion of its common stock, funded by cash from operations, without a termination date and subject to suspension or discontinuation.&lt;SEP&gt;The Repurchase Program is an authorization for AMD to repurchase up to $12 billion of its common stock, funded by cash from operations, without a termination date and subject to suspension or discontinuation.&lt;SEP&gt;The Repurchase Program is an initiative by AMD to repurchase up to $14 billion of its common stock, funded by cash from operations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Repurchase Program is an initiative by AMD to repurchase up to $14 billion of its common stock, funded by operational cash flow.&lt;SEP&gt;A repurchase program is a strategy used by companies to buy back their own shares from the marketplace, affecting stock supply.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bde81dfa7c0130867695a7023e89cf63&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0a83ce1ab52e2df80576ef179eeec72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42b87cf93df46f504c0e370bbcbc6d94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54b2dd7afb5853f7b9fcb8fff6544b20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4f3a99d3019490d0bf692c1a4227a55</data>
