<node id="Rule 10b5-1 Trading Plans">
  <data key="d0">Rule 10b5-1 Trading Plans</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Rule 10b5-1 Trading Plans are a method defined under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended, for directors or officers to adopt, modify, or terminate trading arrangements.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 10b5-1 Trading Plans are a method for directors and officers to arrange trades in advance according to a set plan, as referenced in the context of AMD's management.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 10b5-1 Trading Plans are a method used by AMD's executives to trade company stock in a manner that satisfies the affirmative defense of Rule 10b5-1(c) under the Exchange Act.</data>
