<node id="IPLA">
  <data key="d0">IPLA</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The IPLA is an agreement that governs the sublicensing rights and revenue sharing between Arm and Arm China.&lt;SEP&gt;The IPLA is an organization that has financial dealings with Arm China, relying on the financial information provided by Arm China for determining payments due.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;The IPLA is a contractual agreement between Arm China and the reporting entity, outlining the terms of their business relationship, including financial reporting, audit rights, and indemnification obligations.&lt;SEP&gt;The IPLA is a contractual agreement between Arm China and the reporting entity, outlining the terms of their business relationship, including financial reporting, audit rights, and indemnification obligations.</data>
