</node>
<node id="Residual Approach">
  <data key="d0">Residual Approach</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Residual Approach is a method used to allocate the transaction price to performance obligations when the standalone selling price is not directly observable.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cost-Plus Margin Approach">
  <data key="d0">Cost-Plus Margin Approach</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Cost-Plus Margin Approach is a method for estimating the standalone selling price based on the cost of the product plus an expected margin.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Macroeconomic Effects">
  <data key="d0">Macroeconomic Effects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Macroeconomic Effects are the influences of large-scale economic factors on financial estimates and business operations, such as geopolitical issues and natural disasters.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5952f8b9b70d6c7a8ac3693a20d7033</data>
