<node id="Pillar Two">
  <data key="d0">Pillar Two</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Pillar Two refers to a global tax agreement by the OECD to set a minimum 15% tax rate for certain multinational enterprises.|&lt;SEP&gt;A global minimum tax policy that the company is monitoring for its impact on the effective income tax rate.&lt;SEP&gt;Pillar Two is a framework developed by the OECD aiming to implement a global minimum tax.&lt;SEP&gt;Global minimum tax initiative being adopted by various jurisdictions.&lt;SEP&gt;Pillar Two is a proposal by the OECD aimed at ensuring a minimum level of taxation for multinational corporations.&lt;SEP&gt;Pillar Two is a proposal by the OECD aimed at ensuring a minimum level of taxation for multinational corporations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05ef57917f6bff8e91ef6130ec6229c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a296116922ea376dbdc0f563507f5547&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa5ffd55eec85058d06665add3afcd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89925cf5f28939f5191ad4f0b95711f6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777380667</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Union">
  <data key="d0">European Union</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Union (EU) is a political and economic union of member states primarily located in Europe. It includes countries that are adjusting their tax and accounting laws in accordance with the OECD's Pillar Two framework. The EU plays a significant role in global political matters, illustrated by its decision to impose sanctions against Russia and Belarus due to the ongoing conflict, highlighting its active engagement in international relations.

In the business context, the European Union is a jurisdiction where compliance with distribution and competition laws is essential. Government regulations within the EU have a profound impact on business operations, making it crucial for companies to navigate the extensive legal landscape shaped by these rules. The EU is also governed by the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), which enforces strict guidelines on data transfer and privacy, significantly affecting global businesses that operate within or engage with the EU market.

Moreover, the European Union has established laws concerning the use of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), reflecting its commitment to regulating emerging technologies with a focus on ethical considerations. This underscores the EU's proactive stance in addressing critical issues from taxation and data privacy to technological advancements. Additionally, the EU maintains political and economic relations with the United States, influencing international business dynamics further. 

Overall, the European Union is characterized by its comprehensive legal framework, which addresses diverse aspects ranging from environmental concerns and sustainability protocols to the regulation of advanced technologies, ensuring its relevance in both regional and global contexts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b16721bd4c3f195f2ea0c219b1a93e14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5dab522fff7a5a27ab17d42eb8613b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-050055b3bc468fa0d183c4f69822f018&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5749c9de1780a43222605dcccf7b84ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e356de4d5460f722f331512046c5047&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7268957cde14a4d3b9ad39486be2220a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789e78a4c56dfc29b3f11f7927499d10&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89925cf5f28939f5191ad4f0b95711f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6757e425a6551576cf75d5c43bed978b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777382116</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
