</node>
<node id="Nasdaq">
  <data key="d0">Nasdaq</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Nasdaq is a prominent American stock exchange that serves as a trading platform for various securities, including the Company's American Depository Shares (ADSs) and Restricted Stock Units (RSUs). It is an essential reference point for determining the fair value of these share-based awards, influencing their pricing and valuation within the market.

As a marketplace, Nasdaq is not only where the organization may be listed but also imposes specific corporate governance rules and listing requirements. Companies seeking to be listed on Nasdaq must ensure compliance with these rules, which include provisions from the Sarbanes-Oxley Act. These requirements apply primarily to the organization's audit committee, ensuring transparency and accountability within listed entities.

Additionally, Nasdaq’s governance rules may vary for foreign private issuers, reflecting the exchange’s adaptability to accommodate a diverse range of companies and their unique needs. Through its structured trading environment and regulatory framework, Nasdaq plays a crucial role in the financial ecosystem, influencing both investor behavior and corporate governance standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1fc03c6340e9f91435287101b7ba57e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9cf777435ca6135f2543fc921d450ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf1bb802539f8961349a60bf6c9b66c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6aeca2a51a3e2732d9a306c9c0622909</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777380714</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monte Carlo Simulation">
  <data key="d0">Monte Carlo Simulation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Monte Carlo Simulation is a method used to estimate the fair value of market conditions component of the awards with Relative TSR-based performance measures.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262485</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Reporting Unit">
  <data key="d0">Reporting Unit</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Reporting Unit is an entity identified for the purpose of assessing goodwill impairment.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Reporting Unit is a component of a company for which discrete financial information is available and used in assessing goodwill for impairment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b79e4b75a425925add250c81fbb9b71</data>
