<node id="ADSs">
  <data key="d0">ADSs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">American Depositary Shares (ADSs) are financial instruments that represent shares in foreign companies, facilitating their trading in U.S. financial markets. They enable non-U.S. companies to list and sell their shares on American stock exchanges, making it easier for U.S. investors to buy and sell these foreign securities. ADSs serve as a bridge in international finance, allowing foreign entities to access the U.S. capital markets while providing American investors with the opportunity to invest in foreign companies.

Market dynamics and the business performance of the companies underlying these ADSs significantly influence their pricing. Fluctuations can arise from corporate actions, governance decisions, and ownership changes associated with significant stakeholders, such as SoftBank Group. Furthermore, these shares are underpinned by specific terms outlined in a Deposit Agreement and are subject to rights under English law. 

Generally, ADSs represent ordinary shares of foreign companies and may be susceptible to price volatility driven by both operational performance and external market conditions. They play a crucial role in enabling cross-border investments, therefore enhancing market accessibility for investors in the U.S.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1fc03c6340e9f91435287101b7ba57e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2b270960deb5554f0e44f652867f7fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3de34ec76f3a0a44857b72c2f6e55416&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea00358d47980b031f36bff739496ce1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2d39980a89a2b136f0a1d2d58d59c86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12e1f77fe538051f6128dd4bc89f0c38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c9786a466ef538bc75df1c91bc31589&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e16505fda28ee8ca6cb7b4381bcec9b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9cf777435ca6135f2543fc921d450ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf1bb802539f8961349a60bf6c9b66c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7a6b22211eb6bb771a84281effb4664c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777380558</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
