<node id="Bureau of Industry and Security">
  <data key="d0">Bureau of Industry and Security</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Bureau of Industry and Security, referred to as BIS, is a part of the U.S. Department of Commerce that extended the reach of U.S. export controls on the semiconductor industry.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;The Bureau of Industry and Security is a government agency that issues rules and regulations affecting international trade.&lt;SEP&gt;The Bureau of Industry and Security (BIS) is the U.S. government agency responsible for imposing export controls and regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Bureau of Industry and Security of the U.S. Department of Commerce initiated a Section 232 investigation regarding U.S. imports.&lt;SEP&gt;The Bureau of Industry and Security of the U.S. Department of Commerce initiated a Section 232 investigation regarding U.S. imports.&lt;SEP&gt;The Bureau of Industry and Security (BIS) is responsible for administering export control laws and regulations in the United States.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6430e92774e5a3f258ef2544910d4dd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db3fcbe26ec52d22abad5f9f0435fea6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-050055b3bc468fa0d183c4f69822f018&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed2b32ad29a09feed46df0c963169feb</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777382509</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Implementation of Additional Due Diligence Measures for Advanced Computing Integrated Circuits">
  <data key="d0">Implementation of Additional Due Diligence Measures for Advanced Computing Integrated Circuits</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Implementation of Additional Due Diligence Measures for Advanced Computing Integrated Circuits is an interim final rule published by BIS in January 2025 to limit the manufacturing of advanced node chips by PRC entities outside of China.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262485</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Framework for Artificial Intelligence Diffusion">
  <data key="d0">Framework for Artificial Intelligence Diffusion</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Framework for Artificial Intelligence Diffusion, also known as the AI Diffusion Rule, is an interim final rule introduced in January 2025 to impose worldwide export license requirements on advanced computing products.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262485</data>
