<node id="Open-Source Software">
  <data key="d0">Open-Source Software</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Open-Source Software is software whose source code is made available to the public, allowing anyone to view, use, and modify it.&lt;SEP&gt;Open-Source Software is publicly available software governed by licenses that impose obligations on users who distribute derivative works, potentially affecting the business if not complied with.&lt;SEP&gt;Open-Source Software is publicly available software governed by licenses that impose obligations on users who distribute derivative works, potentially affecting the business if not complied with.&lt;SEP&gt;Open-Source Software is software with source code that can be publicly accessed, modified, and distributed, possibly requiring licensing under open-source terms.</data>
