<node id="SoftBank Group">
  <data key="d0">SoftBank Group</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">SoftBank Group is a multinational conglomerate renowned for its extensive investments primarily in technology and telecommunications. As a controlling entity, SoftBank Group possesses approximately 87.1% ownership of the total issued share capital in various companies, notably Arm China, through its ownership of Acetone Limited. This significant stake establishes SoftBank Group as a major investor with considerable influence over corporate governance and operational oversight.

The company's influence is further amplified by its rights under the Shareholder Governance Agreement, which may lead to potential conflicts of interest with other stakeholders, including holders of American Depositary Shares (ADSs). SoftBank Group actively participates in advising associated companies, particularly in designing chips and forming commercial partnerships, reinforcing its integrative strategy within the technology sector.

In its relationship with Arm China, SoftBank Group’s oversight capabilities are crucial; however, this control may be subject to variations in Arm China's governance structures. The conglomerate holds substantial equity interests and pre-emptive rights in various shareholder agreements, which further underscores its ability to impact financial transactions, thereby affecting market dynamics related to affiliated securities.

SoftBank Group's status as a controlled foreign corporation (CFC) is affirmed by its ownership of more than 50% of ordinary shares, highlighting its pivotal role in shaping corporate strategies. Its ability to manage and potentially transfer its holdings indicates a dynamic approach in investment maneuvers while maintaining a significant market presence. Additionally, the organization wields registration rights that could influence the market value of its ADSs and other financial instruments, reflecting its broad impact across various sectors and investment landscapes.

Overall, SoftBank Group stands as a major entity in global investments with a focus on innovation and strategic development, possessing the capacity to affect governance, ownership structures, and market strategies across its subsidiaries and affiliated businesses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca207bb382651453029b45cb72e9feff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2b270960deb5554f0e44f652867f7fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9d385d153b391ba0f835b4e1b0862be&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3de34ec76f3a0a44857b72c2f6e55416&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-433cb292a4d13d00542cbbad21ff7c8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0d1065649bee800c972122f59f7fc8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2d39980a89a2b136f0a1d2d58d59c86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12e1f77fe538051f6128dd4bc89f0c38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66a91d342b5fd2e4bb339a793a46f87d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e16505fda28ee8ca6cb7b4381bcec9b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9cf777435ca6135f2543fc921d450ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-588c85ac2130c08f6763faa2a55cecd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-18f76dffaa65f39c56d463cfdba66ecb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caf1bb802539f8961349a60bf6c9b66c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-520988de7bd26059b457c267986b647d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-160cdbc68f2192977c5b096f393e5c57</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777380627</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
