<node id="Operating Cash Flows">
  <data key="d0">Operating Cash Flows</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Operating cash flows are a measure of the amount of cash generated or used by a company's operating activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Operating cash flows refer to the cash generated or used by a company's primary business operations.&lt;SEP&gt;Operating cash flows indicate the cash that a company generates from its normal business operations, considered in the context of existing customers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25056dc4aba0a40a47c338bbf9630c33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a5582252ed15279da3f293d02cea1b9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777382510</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Finite-Lived Purchased Intangible Assets">
  <data key="d0">Finite-Lived Purchased Intangible Assets</data>
  <data key="d1">financialasset</data>
  <data key="d2">Finite-lived purchased intangible assets are non-tangible assets with a limited useful life, which are subject to impairment testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Finite-Lived Purchased Intangible Assets are assets that are tested for impairment based on forecasted undiscounted future cash flows.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b79e4b75a425925add250c81fbb9b71</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777306896</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Undiscounted Future Cash Flows">
  <data key="d0">Undiscounted Future Cash Flows</data>
  <data key="d1">financialmetric</data>
  <data key="d2">Undiscounted future cash flows refer to the projected cash inflows from an asset or group of assets without adjusting for the time value of money.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777306896</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Carrying Value">
  <data key="d0">Carrying Value</data>
  <data key="d1">financialmetric</data>
  <data key="d2">The carrying value of an asset is the value at which it is reported on a company's balance sheet.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777306896</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fair Value">
  <data key="d0">Fair Value</data>
  <data key="d1">financialmetric</data>
  <data key="d2">Fair value is the price that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7df88c2c7b38c5eb12580560b4e0dc2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a5582252ed15279da3f293d02cea1b9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777306896</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Income Approach">
  <data key="d0">Income Approach</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The income approach is a method of estimating the fair value of an asset by considering the present value of its future cash flows.&lt;SEP&gt;The Income Approach is a valuation method used to estimate the fair value of a reporting unit through discounted cash flow analysis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b79e4b75a425925add250c81fbb9b71</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777306896</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Relief-From-Royalty Method">
  <data key="d0">Relief-From-Royalty Method</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The relief-from-royalty method is a technique used to estimate the fair value of an asset by calculating the savings in royalty payments that ownership of the asset provides.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777306896</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multi-Period Excess-Earnings Method">
  <data key="d0">Multi-Period Excess-Earnings Method</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The multi-period excess-earnings method is a technique used to estimate the fair value of an intangible asset by calculating the excess earnings generated over a period of time.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777306896</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PCB Business">
  <data key="d0">PCB Business</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The PCB business is a unit within the company that focuses on printed circuit board production.&lt;SEP&gt;PCB Business is a segment of the company that experienced a long-term forecast deterioration, leading to impairment tests and a pre-reorganization goodwill impairment charge.&lt;SEP&gt;The PCB Business is part of the company's reportable segment that experienced a deterioration in its long-term forecast.&lt;SEP&gt;The PCB Business is part of the company's operations, which experienced a deterioration in its long-term forecast.&lt;SEP&gt;The PCB Business is part of the company and is experiencing a long-term forecast deterioration, leading to impairment charges.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8c3943d4fcccf1ae19651cf71f87bf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b79e4b75a425925add250c81fbb9b71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19032b9d0addd28842932a48ea8fd697&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d780eacfb91e291d22055bf3aca31fa3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777307810</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Display Business">
  <data key="d0">Display Business</data>
  <data key="d1">businesssector</data>
  <data key="d2">The Display business is a unit within the company that focuses on display technology production.&lt;SEP&gt;The Display Business is a sector from which the company decided to exit in March 2024 by announcing the end of manufacturing of most Display products.&lt;SEP&gt;The Display Business is a sector in which the company decided to exit in the third quarter of fiscal 2024 due to a customer-related decision.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e28f2689bd6a5fe65b47f7c31f1a8adc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db3fcbe26ec52d22abad5f9f0435fea6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5d617bafedeb6760bbc60c5e3993fb7</data>
