</node>
<node id="Tax Valuation Allowances">
  <data key="d0">Tax Valuation Allowances</data>
  <data key="d1">financialmetric</data>
  <data key="d2">Tax valuation allowances are provisions made against deferred tax assets to reflect the company's best estimate of the portion of the assets that is not expected to be realized.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777306896</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="California Credit Carry-Forwards">
  <data key="d0">California Credit Carry-Forwards</data>
  <data key="d1">financialasset</data>
  <data key="d2">California credit carry-forwards are tax credits that can be carried forward from one tax year to the next to offset future tax liabilities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777306896</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Revenues">
  <data key="d0">Revenues</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Revenues refer to the total income generated from the main operations of a company.&lt;SEP&gt;The income derived from the sales of our products, which could be affected by various factors including product acceptance and pricing.&lt;SEP&gt;Revenues are the total income generated from the sales of goods or services related to the company's primary operations.&lt;SEP&gt;Revenues represent the income generated by the company, which is affected by various factors including customer base concentration, capital equipment procurement schedules, and foreign currency exchange rates.&lt;SEP&gt;Revenues represent the income generated from the company's sales of products and services.&lt;SEP&gt;Revenues represent the income generated from the company's sales of products and services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cef59817c38511355f56938f73f6db2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25056dc4aba0a40a47c338bbf9630c33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-940cea73a3ab3826472368a5d0f388bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1329332311e82d0b2cc6f7232bfaa092&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ade0a30743a7edf4b6eaaebdf38aaaa2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777380681</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Uncertain Tax Positions">
  <data key="d0">Uncertain Tax Positions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Uncertain tax positions are tax-related financial statements that are subject to judgment and estimation due to their uncertain nature.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777306896</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Complex Tax Laws">
  <data key="d0">Complex Tax Laws</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Complex tax laws are the intricate legal frameworks that the Company must apply when calculating its effective tax rate and deferred tax assets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777306896</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Future Taxable Income">
  <data key="d0">Future Taxable Income</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Future taxable income is the estimated income that the Company anticipates earning in the future, which is used in the calculation of deferred tax assets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37906de44c22f23501372f2b90cd5aa7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
