  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Working capital is a financial metric representing the entity's short-term liquidity, calculated as of June 30, 2025, and showing an increase compared to the previous year.&lt;SEP&gt;Working Capital as of December 31, 2024, was $5.63 billion, representing an increase of $264.0 million from June 30, 2024.&lt;SEP&gt;Working Capital is a financial metric that funds the repurchase programs of ANET.</data>
