  <data key="d0">Liquidity and Capital Resources</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Liquidity and Capital Resources is a section of the report that discusses the company's strong cash flow generation and strategy of returning excess cash to stockholders.&lt;SEP&gt;Liquidity and capital resources are the company's principal sources of liquidity, including cash, cash equivalents, and marketable securities.&lt;SEP&gt;Liquidity and Capital Resources refers to the company's principal sources of liquidity, which include cash, cash equivalents, marketable securities, and cash generated from operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c0f7533f1c0231555ac5ae30f4d37842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88fbdee009d132142f267759b80b8fcd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69f1af12f4eafcde14c51426aec9aa50</data>
