<node id="IP Rights">
  <data key="d0">IP Rights</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Intellectual Property Rights (IP Rights) are legal rights associated with creations of the mind, which include inventions, designs, and brand elements. These rights provide creators and companies with control over the use of their original works, ensuring that they can protect their innovations from infringement or unauthorized use. The maintenance of IP Rights is crucial for companies to uphold their competitive edge in the market.

Organizations such as KLA and ARM recognize the importance of IP Rights in securing their proprietary products and brand integrity. For KLA, there is a specific concern regarding the loss of IP Rights due to potential cyber-related security breaches. Meanwhile, ARM emphasizes the need to enforce these rights actively to safeguard its proprietary offerings. Therefore, IP Rights are not only significant for legal protection but are also essential for the success and sustainability of companies in a competitive business environment.&lt;SEP&gt;IP rights refer to legal rights that protect inventions, designs, brands, and other intellectual property, crucial for business success.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e74b16856b8a1a3ddf8e77f75d7175ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a23fd7a348fc3f448641e9ef7d5be33a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3de34ec76f3a0a44857b72c2f6e55416&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f68eec3cfcff91b0a5074f99debbfc89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789e78a4c56dfc29b3f11f7927499d10&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f075ac62ff92ae30a48578e40574de9</data>
