  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Commerce refers to the U.S. Department of Commerce, which issues rules and regulations affecting the company's ability to sell products and provide services, particularly to China.&lt;SEP&gt;Commerce refers to the U.S. Department of Commerce, responsible for publishing the BIS Rules and regulations on trade.&lt;SEP&gt;Commerce is an organization within the U.S. responsible for initiating investigations into the effects of imports on national security.</data>
