<node id="2022 BIS Rules">
  <data key="d0">2022 BIS Rules</data>
  <data key="d1">regulation</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2022 BIS Rules are regulations published by the U.S. Department of Commerce that impose restrictions on the sale, shipment, and support of certain equipment and business conduct, primarily with China.&lt;SEP&gt;The 2022 BIS Rules are regulations introduced by the U.S. Department of Commerce that restrict trade with certain companies in China.&lt;SEP&gt;The 2022 BIS Rules imposed export licensing requirements for certain U.S. semiconductor and high-performance computing technology for use in China.</data>
