<node id="U.S. Tariffs">
  <data key="d0">U.S. Tariffs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The U.S. Tariffs are a series of trade restrictions implemented by the U.S. on imported goods, impacting various industries and countries.&lt;SEP&gt;U.S. Tariffs are taxes imposed by the U.S. government on imported goods, mentioned in the context of trade restrictions.&lt;SEP&gt;U.S. tariffs include taxes imposed on imports; specifically mentioned are semiconductor-related tariffs affecting financial conditions and supply chain.&lt;SEP&gt;U.S. tariffs include taxes imposed on imports; specifically mentioned are semiconductor-related tariffs affecting financial conditions and supply chain.&lt;SEP&gt;U.S. Tariffs are government-imposed taxes that may negatively affect global economic conditions and the business of the entity.&lt;SEP&gt;U.S. Tariffs are taxes imposed by the United States on imports, which have implications for international trade, particularly with China and Mexico.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd0c155e1db1c75ce34ca7f10841ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69ff95667fb52350500821b847289ef6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9046829702051c016224dd2ad2934dd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48398f86ee66960c2b40a409c49e55e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed2b32ad29a09feed46df0c963169feb</data>
