<node id="Economic Sanctions">
  <data key="d0">Economic Sanctions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Economic Sanctions are trade restrictions imposed by countries, affecting international commerce and economic relations.&lt;SEP&gt;Economic sanctions are measures imposed to restrict trade and financial transactions with particular countries or individuals.&lt;SEP&gt;Economic sanctions are measures imposed to restrict trade and financial transactions with particular countries or individuals.&lt;SEP&gt;Economic Sanctions are measures that can affect international trade and the Company's ability to operate in certain countries.&lt;SEP&gt;Economic Sanctions are laws prohibiting the shipment of products and services to embargoed countries and sanctioned entities.&lt;SEP&gt;Economic Sanctions are measures implemented by governments to restrict economic transactions, often impacting international business operations.</data>
