  <data key="d2">Cyberattacks are potential security events that could lead to breaches of Arm's security controls and unauthorized access to data.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyberattacks refer to various malicious attempts to compromise or disrupt information technology systems, including ransomware, phishing, and denial of service attacks.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyberattacks refer to malicious attempts to breach information technology systems and compromise data security.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyberattacks are incidents involving unauthorized access or attempts to exploit vulnerabilities in the organization's information technology systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyberattacks refer to various malicious attempts to compromise or disrupt information technology systems, including ransomware, phishing, and denial of service attacks.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyberattacks refer to malicious attempts to breach information technology systems and compromise data security.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyberattacks are incidents involving unauthorized access or attempts to exploit vulnerabilities in the organization's information technology systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a09335734e89edd5d8f3e04bd3466cd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe9aa0edeb1f35465d1cc96dcdb61a4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd14fb5ebc4062cace68cd9e6a1bf084&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61f3bc12aec2296a1fa9ad0ee19d3d6d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777380650</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
