<node id="Broadcom">
  <data key="d0">Broadcom</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Broadcom Inc. is a prominent global technology leader recognized for its extensive work in designing, developing, and supplying semiconductor and semiconductor-based solutions, as well as infrastructure software solutions. The company has established itself as an industry leader in supporting the expansion of the Arm compute platform and is actively partnering with Arm to facilitate AI transformation.

In addition to its core semiconductor business, Broadcom has been heavily involved in mergers and acquisitions, significantly expanding its product portfolio through strategic acquisitions, including Brocade Communications and VMware. This growth strategy underscores Broadcom's commitment to enhancing its offerings and market position.

As a leading merchant silicon vendor, Broadcom plays a critical role in providing switching chips that are integral to various products across the industry. The company also engages in financial strategies such as planning share repurchase programs and distributing dividends to its stockholders, reflecting its solid financial performance and commitment to delivering value to investors. 

Overall, Broadcom Inc. stands out as a multifaceted technology company that not only leads in semiconductor solutions but also actively shapes the future of technology through partnerships, strategic acquisitions, and stakeholder engagement.&lt;SEP&gt;Broadcom is a company from which Arista Networks acquired the VeloCloud SD-WAN Portfolio.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e303b18ab63b26668de99eef62a26b7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb82fb0b57380bdf7abd3bbcae084048&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5128d467897e9a6a1ea6d801c0966d6e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf438b7e4564db1875e01c22f58140c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-369a5552d7a3758ad27f4b784ffe7595&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c84b525ec6385a6df80b84b52431bb29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-daa7b8544edadd0f701ab9d8efd26b8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31dc5de5694e64a393f6bb8bdb1ee1fe</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777382155</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Google">
  <data key="d0">Google</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Google is an industry leader supporting the expansion of the Arm compute platform and has built custom Axion CPUs on the Arm architecture.&lt;SEP&gt;Google is a technology company that collaborates with Intel on deploying advanced Intel Xeon processors across its cloud services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e303b18ab63b26668de99eef62a26b7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92916718cb73d1b7ba5306ed1ae35864</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777381654</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Marvell">
  <data key="d0">Marvell</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Marvell is an industry leader supporting the expansion of the Arm compute platform and partnering with Arm for AI infrastructure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e303b18ab63b26668de99eef62a26b7e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777308127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Micron">
  <data key="d0">Micron</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Micron is an industry leader supporting the expansion of the Arm compute platform, with a focus on compute and memory working together.&lt;SEP&gt;Micron is a company whose products have faced export controls imposed by the Chinese government.&lt;SEP&gt;Micron is a company whose products are affected by Chinese government controls on technology.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e303b18ab63b26668de99eef62a26b7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b85ec976f34913889413e19b8bcf3a78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec5ba923d7a24c9eaf76ee9457a79656</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777382081</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Microsoft Azure">
  <data key="d0">Microsoft Azure</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Microsoft Azure is an industry leader supporting the expansion of the Arm compute platform, with Azure Cobalt family of CPUs built on Neoverse CSS.&lt;SEP&gt;Microsoft Azure is a platform that has developed the Azure Cobalt family of CPUs, built on Neoverse CSS, as stated by Rani Borkar.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e303b18ab63b26668de99eef62a26b7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0fc487cdc1541b708566fbf837bf0441</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777308127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Arm AGI CPU">
  <data key="d0">Arm AGI CPU</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Arm AGI CPU is the first Arm-designed data center CPU for agentic AI infrastructure, offering more than 2x performance per rack compared to x86 platforms. It is expected to be the foundation for agentic data centers and is backed by a strong global ecosystem.&lt;SEP&gt;The Arm AGI CPU is a product that marks the next phase of Arm's evolution into data center silicon, designed for AI infrastructure at scale.&lt;SEP&gt;The Arm AGI CPU is a purpose-built AI compute platform that creates new opportunities for deeper collaboration across silicon design, memory integration, and manufacturing innovation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e303b18ab63b26668de99eef62a26b7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0fc487cdc1541b708566fbf837bf0441&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2d1f6742e80ed84d267cfe46fa7c9e31</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777308127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Graviton">
  <data key="d0">Graviton</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Graviton is a server CPU built by AWS in partnership with Arm, known for its better price/performance ratio.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e303b18ab63b26668de99eef62a26b7e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777308127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Axion CPUs">
  <data key="d0">Axion CPUs</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Axion CPUs are Google's custom CPUs built on the Arm architecture, designed for energy efficiency and scalability.</data>
