  <data key="d0">In-Process Research and Development</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">In-process research and development (IPR&amp;D) is initially capitalized as an indefinite-lived intangible asset in connection with acquisitions and reclassified as amortizable purchased intangible assets upon completion of the underlying project.&lt;SEP&gt;In-process research and development (IPR&amp;D) is initially capitalized as an indefinite-lived intangible asset in connection with acquisitions and reclassified as amortizable purchased intangible assets upon completion of the underlying project.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b02dd03910eba2f64d7717819c0ef1bc</data>
