<node id="Restructuring and Other Charges">
  <data key="d0">Restructuring and Other Charges</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Restructuring and Other Charges refer to a range of non-recurring operating expenses primarily associated with the reorganization of a company's operations. These charges mainly include compensation costs related to employee exit programs, costs from intellectual property (IP) litigation, the alignment of global manufacturing operations, rationalization of product development program expenses, facility and lease abandonments, asset impairments, and other associated exit costs.

For the fiscal year 2025, Restructuring and Other Charges amounted to $591 million. This represents a significant decrease of 61% in comparison to previous periods, largely attributed to reduced employee termination costs following the integration of the VMware business. The overall financial impact of these charges has been considerable, affecting the company's financial performance.

Furthermore, these charges encompass various aspects of reorganizing a company’s operations, reflecting the transient nature of these costs and their role in restructuring efforts aimed at enhancing operational efficiency and aligning resources more effectively with ongoing business needs. Overall, Restructuring and Other Charges serve as a critical measure of the financial effects stemming from organizational changes within a company.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b02dd03910eba2f64d7717819c0ef1bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7df88c2c7b38c5eb12580560b4e0dc2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99ce04c1c520fc4abd8bec8e5e164c28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eddee67b369c229f33b13b2d39309da9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-063cbc70b0b679d3caa2cb95ecd87963&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7953fde635f26daca7c212affde7869c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777381680</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
