  <data key="d3">chunk-7df88c2c7b38c5eb12580560b4e0dc2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-923b6a774533b6ee182ac5d5b97611cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c17cee8b5d4c0058ad449ca8d769b9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bbc7bb48e6d4943b055b0203ce8adb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69f1af12f4eafcde14c51426aec9aa50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d1a6abe12ff0346c565b00be1a824f</data>
  <data key="d2">Net revenue is impacted by the cost of revenue in determining the gross margin.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Cost of revenue includes the expenses associated with manufacturing products and providing services, which increased by $725.2 million, or 28.9%, for the year ended December 31, 2025 compared to 2024.&lt;SEP&gt;Total cost of revenue for the year ended December 31, 2024, was $2,511.8 million, a 12.6% increase from the previous year.&lt;SEP&gt;Cost of revenue is a financial metric that represents the total expenses directly associated with the production of the company's products/services, which increased to $3,237.0 million in 2025, up by 28.9% from $2,511.8 million in 2024.&lt;SEP&gt;The cost of revenue increased by $282.0 million, driven by increased product and service revenues.&lt;SEP&gt;Cost of revenue encompasses the expenses related to sales of products and services, impacting financial performance.</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
