  <data key="d2">The increase in research and development expense is primarily due to higher stock-based compensation.&lt;SEP&gt;Stock-Based Compensation is a method of compensating employees using shares of stock or stock options.&lt;SEP&gt;Tax benefits attributable to stock-based compensation affected the effective tax rate.&lt;SEP&gt;Stock-Based Compensation is a form of payment to employees for which a company sets aside shares of its stock or the right to purchase such shares as part of the employee's compensation.&lt;SEP&gt;Stock-Based Compensation is the cost associated with the granting of stock-based awards to employees, which is recognized as an expense over the service period.&lt;SEP&gt;Stock-based compensation outlines the capital used to reward employees, impacting tax calculations and cash flows.&lt;SEP&gt;Stock-based compensation represents costs associated with equity awards given to employees, which increased during fiscal 2025.</data>
