  <data key="d2">Industry Standards are the established norms and protocols that guide the development and manufacturing of products in the industry.&lt;SEP&gt;Industry standards are benchmarks that the company's products are designed to conform to.&lt;SEP&gt;Industry Standards are benchmarks or protocols that guide the development and functionality of products in various sectors, influencing their adoption and implementation.&lt;SEP&gt;Industry Standards are the established norms and protocols that guide the development and manufacturing of products in the industry.&lt;SEP&gt;Industry standards are benchmarks that the company's products are designed to conform to.&lt;SEP&gt;Industry Standards are benchmarks or protocols that guide the development and functionality of products in various sectors, influencing their adoption and implementation.&lt;SEP&gt;Industry standards are established norms that the company's products must comply with to interoperate efficiently with other networking equipment.</data>
