<node id="Deferred Revenue">
  <data key="d0">Deferred Revenue</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Deferred Revenue is the revenue recognized in advance of service delivery or product shipment, which impacts the company's cash flows.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred Revenue is a liability account that represents revenue for which the company has been paid but has not yet provided the service or product to the customer.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred Revenue is a financial data point representing the revenue received in advance for goods or services that have not yet been delivered or provided.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-42aa9c7f7d4ca12621cf2af559e1aa29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88fbdee009d132142f267759b80b8fcd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f683649d33f58f1759bf7001deddc60</data>
