<node id="Network Infrastructure">
  <data key="d0">Network Infrastructure</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Network infrastructure is a system of networks that may be affected by economic conditions and spending.&lt;SEP&gt;Network Infrastructure refers to the technology and services that support widespread networking, potentially impacted by economic factors and customer spending.&lt;SEP&gt;A system of networks that provides communication channels between users and connects different devices or services.&lt;SEP&gt;Network Infrastructure refers to the systems and hardware that customers may upgrade, which can be delayed, thus extending the sales cycle for the company's products.&lt;SEP&gt;Network infrastructure encompasses the networks, servers, software, and operating systems that the company's products must interoperate with.&lt;SEP&gt;The network infrastructure industry involves the hardware and services for network construction and management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2603d7a1a4143ae5d683f57941a3ca2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-910ac36ac071842241018eea8ce214a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7de6378b79bb633b98b31314e541a4cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6646d6be107845318b9e01fd74b6a79&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ca4353a43bcb8671d00174ee0da3be0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6837c4686c704cf481e701435fa08a62</data>
